  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pain is the most prevalent non-motor symptom in Parkinson disease, and the motor improvement
      not always is related to the pain improvement with the medication treatment. By this, we are
      testing a non-invasive method called transcranial magnetic stimulation as an alternative to
      treat pain related to Parkinson disease. This technique can lead to either inhibitory or
      excitatory effects in brain circuits depending on stimulation parameters, and is known to
      provide analgesic effects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
